# Aviation Replacement Parts for CC-138 Twin Otter 
## Government of Canada Tender Announcement

The Department of National Defence intends to procure aviation replacement parts for the CC-138 Twin Otter. The solicitation number is W8485-258183/A and is open to Qualified Supply Arrangement (SA) Holders of Supply Arrangement W8485-184741 series.

### Tender Summary

* **Tender Identification Number (TIN):** W8485-258183/A
* **Submission Deadline:** June 13, 2024, at 14:00:00
* **Procurement Approach:** Competitive with a Solicitation Notice
* **Evaluation Criteria:** Highest Combined Rating of Technical Merit and Price
* **Expected Contract Start Date:** June 28, 2024
* **Expected Contract End Date:** July 12, 2024

### Tender Documentation and Requirements

The tender documents will be e-mailed directly to the Qualified SA Holders who are being invited to bid on this requirement. Bidders are advised that the Government Electronic Tendering Service (GETS) is not responsible for the distribution of the tender documents.

### Contact Information

For any inquiries or requests for information regarding this tender, please contact:

Aerospace Equipment Program Management (DGAEPM)
Department of National Defence (DND)
455, Boulvard de la carrière, Gatineau (QC) J8Y 6V7
Ivan.Khanzadeev@forces.gc.ca

### Procurement Details

The procurement is for 6 item(s) for the CC-138 Twin Otter for the Department of National Defence (DND), Directorate of Aerospace Procurement (DAP) 4. The tender is open to the following companies who have been invited to submit a proposal:

* CASP
* Simex Defence Inc.
* Genaire Limited
* Bristow
* Canada West Avionics
* Pratt & Whitney Canada Corp.
* Aero Technical Components Inc.
* JHT Defense Inc.
* B S F (Business Solutions Fasteners) International Inc.
* Honeywell Ltd

### Contracting Entity

The contracting entity is the Department of National Defence (DND) and the procurement is for a Supply Arrangement (SA) under the W8485-184741 series. The expected contract start date is June 28, 2024, and the expected contract end date is July 12, 2024.

### Notice of Proposed Procurement (NPP)
